{
  "stem": "10181.4",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they had these watchtowers where they used to fire-- they kept on firing in the air.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I think it was to scare us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We-- I didn't know it was-- nobody knew they were firing into the air, but they were, you know, to make a lot of noise shooting.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Nobody was shot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was just a scare tactic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then we were put up in barracks, and these were completely different from Westerbork, you know, because the little food we had with us, of course, we had ate-- we consumed most of it during the-- during the trip.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We did-- we got nothing during the trip except some water, and then when we got to Westerbork, they-- they sort of gave us-- gave us-- gave you [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Not to-- to Bergen-Belsen, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They gave you a slice of bread and some-- some soup, some-- some, which was like, you know, turnip soup, whatever it was, watery soup.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That was the food we got when we arrived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And you know, the men and women were separated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I was separated from my sister at first.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And it was-- you know, it was sort of-- it was very scary because we didn't know what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And we knew that the only people who were watching us now were the Germans, were the SS, nobody else, OK.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because in Westerbork, you saw very few Germans inside the camp usually.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Only on the days of the trains, but otherwise you didn't.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [? first-- ?] the next day, they-- of course, there was role call, and then they assigned work.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Work was assigned, and the few children, we were not assigned any work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was not-- we didn't really know what to do with ourselves.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
